#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:36
msgid "Lesson Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:39
msgid "This fish is swimming."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:41
msgid "Added **Fish** sprite, **Star** sprite and **Underwater1** backdrop image."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:47
msgid ""
"Let the Fish appear at the coordinates (-240,120), and then let it swim "
"left and right."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:49
msgid ""
"Use the 「**if on edge, bounce**」 block to make the Fish sprite fold back "
"from the edge. When it hits the wall, it will fold back in the opposite "
"direction to the original."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:56
msgid "This Star is rising."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:58
msgid ""
"Let the Star appear at (0,-120). If we press the ``←`` or ``→`` key on "
"the keyboard, it will go left and right."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:60
msgid ""
"We use the 「**key ... pressed**」block to determine the keyboard, and use "
"「**change x by ...**」 to move the sprite."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:66
msgid ""
"Next, launch the Star. If the space bar is pressed, the y coordinate "
"value of the Star sprite will increase, and the Star sprite will rise."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:72
msgid ""
"Something is wrong. The Star sprite should continue to rise until it "
"reaches the height of the Fish sprite (remember? The y coordinate we set "
"for Fish is 120) and then return."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:78
msgid "Now，It looks better."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:81
msgid "Fish hit by a Star."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:83
msgid ""
"After the Star rises, before returning to the bottom, you need to use a "
"「**touch...**」block to determine whether it hits the Fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:85
msgid ""
"When the Star sprite hits the Fish sprite, we need to tell the Fish "
"sprite about this and let it do the corresponding behavior-change its "
"shape."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:87
msgid ""
"We set up a \"Hit\" broadcast. This broadcast will tell the entire "
"program that something called \"Hit\" has happened. All sprite and even "
"the backdrop can hear this broadcast and respond accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:93
msgid ""
"Back to the programming interface of the Fish sprite, use a 「**when I "
"receive...**」 block to receive the \"Hit\" broadcast, and then use "
"「**Next costume**」to change your form."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:100
msgid "Calculate the score!"
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:102
msgid ""
"To make the game more interesting! Add a scoring mechanism. When you "
"click the green flag, the score will be reset to zero. When a \"hit\" "
"event occurs, the score will increase by 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:109
msgid ""
"This does not involve the calculation of sprites and backdrops. We tend "
"to put such codes in backdrops."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:112
msgid "Countdown!"
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:114
msgid ""
"Add a time mechanism. When the green flag is clicked, the timer is set to"
" 30s, and then decreases by 1 every second until the event is reset to "
"zero to end the game."
msgstr ""

#: ../hit_the_magic_fish.rst:116
msgid ""
"But if you hear the \"Hit\" broadcast, let the timer increase by one to "
"increase the game time."
msgstr ""

